abstract: Senator Kevin Cramer and several other Republicans took advantage of the break to praise the arguments made by President Trump’s lawyers in the afternoon.
snippet: Senator Kevin Cramer and several other Republicans took advantage of the break to praise the arguments made by President Trump’s lawyers in the afternoon.
lead_paragraph: The 45-minute dinner break at the Senate impeachment trial featured selections from Chick-fil-A, a choice that reminded Senator Kevin Cramer, Republican of North Dakota, of his earlier tenure in the more proletarian lower chamber.

abstract: A Washington visit by Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu to discuss a long-awaited Middle East peace plan lent a surprise boost on Monday to his main political rival, who secured a separate meeting with U.S. President Donald Trump.
snippet: A Washington visit by Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu to discuss a long-awaited Middle East peace plan lent a surprise boost on Monday to his main political rival, who secured a separate meeting with U.S. President Donald Trump.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A Washington visit by Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu to discuss a long-awaited Middle East peace plan lent a surprise boost on Monday to his main political rival, who secured a separate meeting with U.S. President Donald Trump.
headline_main: Trump Meeting Lends PR Boost to Political Rival of Israel's Netanyahu
headline_print_headline: Trump Meeting Lends PR Boost to Political Rival of Israel's Netanyahu

abstract: The U.S. Supreme Court gave the go-ahead on Monday for one of President Donald Trump's hardline immigration policies, allowing his administration to implement a rule denying legal permanent residency to certain immigrants deemed likely to require government assistance in the future.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The U.S. Supreme Court gave the go-ahead on Monday for one of President Donald Trump's hardline immigration policies, allowing his administration to implement a rule denying legal permanent residency to certain immigrants deemed likely to require government assistance in the future.
headline_main: U.S. Supreme Court Lets Hardline Trump Immigration Policy Take Effect
headline_print_headline: U.S. Supreme Court Lets Hardline Trump Immigration Policy Take Effect

abstract: Kenneth Starr, the lawyer whose investigation led to the impeachment of former U.S. President Bill Clinton in 1998, told the Senate on Monday that the process was happening all too often in what he called an "age of impeachment" as he spoke in defense of his client, President Donald Trump.
snippet: Kenneth Starr, the lawyer whose investigation led to the impeachment of former U.S. President Bill Clinton in 1998, told the Senate on Monday that the process was happening all too often in what he called an "age of impeachment" as he spoke in def...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Kenneth Starr, the lawyer whose investigation led to the impeachment of former U.S. President Bill Clinton in 1998, told the Senate on Monday that the process was happening all too often in what he called an "age of impeachment" as he spoke in defense of his client, President Donald Trump.
headline_main: Starr, Lawyer Who Pursued Clinton and Now Defends Trump, Rails Against Impeachment
headline_print_headline: Starr, Lawyer Who Pursued Clinton and Now Defends Trump, Rails Against Impeachment

abstract: As he draws each image, he jots down notes about color, because he must exit the chamber before filling in his drawings with watercolor.
snippet: As he draws each image, he jots down notes about color, because he must exit the chamber before filling in his drawings with watercolor.
lead_paragraph: Courtroom artist Art Lien sketches with a thin mechanical pencil from his perch in the Senate press gallery, where he is covering the trial for The Times. “People move around and things change, so it’s nice to be able to erase,” he said.
headline_main: Sketches capture the action in the Senate.

abstract: Nigeria had no warning from Washington that it could be added to the list of countries subject to a U.S. travel ban, information minister Lai Mohammed said on Monday, adding such a move would be "hasty" and send the wrong signal to investors.
snippet: Nigeria had no warning from Washington that it could be added to the list of countries subject to a U.S. travel ban, information minister Lai Mohammed said on Monday, adding such a move would be "hasty" and send the wrong signal to investors.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — Nigeria had no warning from Washington that it could be added to the list of countries subject to a U.S. travel ban, information minister Lai Mohammed said on Monday, adding such a move would be "hasty" and send the wrong signal to investors.
headline_main: Nigeria Had No Warning on Potential U.S. Travel Ban: Minister
headline_print_headline: Nigeria Had No Warning on Potential U.S. Travel Ban: Minister

abstract: Iowa caucusgoers aren’t just asking about the one issue that’s dominating the headlines.
snippet: Iowa caucusgoers aren’t just asking about the one issue that’s dominating the headlines.
lead_paragraph: MARSHALLTOWN, Iowa — With three jurors in the impeachment trial traipsing about Iowa this past weekend, you’d expect someone — anyone! — planning to attend the Iowa caucuses to ask the presidential candidates about impeachment.

abstract: U.S. Republican Senator Mitt Romney said on Monday that it was "increasingly likely" at least four Republican senators would join Democrats in calling for John Bolton, the former White House national security adviser, to testify in the Senate impeachment trial of U.S. President Donald Trump.
snippet: U.S. Republican Senator Mitt Romney said on Monday that it was "increasingly likely" at least four Republican senators would join Democrats in calling for John Bolton, the former White House national security adviser, to testify in the Senate impe...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — U.S. Republican Senator Mitt Romney said on Monday that it was "increasingly likely" at least four Republican senators would join Democrats in calling for John Bolton, the former White House national security adviser, to testify in the Senate impeachment trial of U.S. President Donald Trump.
headline_main: 'Increasingly Likely' Republican Senators to Back Call for Bolton to Testify: Romney
headline_print_headline: 'Increasingly Likely' Republican Senators to Back Call for Bolton to Testify: Romney

abstract: Israeli centrist party leader Benny Gantz on Monday praised U.S. President Donald Trump for drafting a Middle East peace deal and committed to help implementing it after Israel's March election.
snippet: Israeli centrist party leader Benny Gantz on Monday praised U.S. President Donald Trump for drafting a Middle East peace deal and committed to help implementing it after Israel's March election.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Israeli centrist party leader Benny Gantz on Monday praised U.S. President Donald Trump for drafting a Middle East peace deal and committed to help implementing it after Israel's March election.
headline_main: Israel's Gantz Praises Trump Peace Plan, Will Work to Implement It After Election
headline_print_headline: Israel's Gantz Praises Trump Peace Plan, Will Work to Implement It After Election

abstract: Politics is about getting power to enact an agenda. And the only way to do that is face-to-face organizing.
snippet: Politics is about getting power to enact an agenda. And the only way to do that is face-to-face organizing.
lead_paragraph: In religion and in politics, participants come together in communities to serve a higher purpose. They worship together to serve God. They join advocacy groups and political party committees to serve their civic duty.
